    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>Known as a vibrant, progressive community, Burlington, Iowa is located near the Mississippi River and its bluffs.  Famous for being the home of Snake Alley, the most crooked alley in the world, Burlington is also a regional center for shopping, education and recreation.  With a considerable amount of parks, there are plenty of trails to discover, by walking, jogging or bicycling.  There are sport complexes, complete with fields for soccer, softball and sand volleyball.  Quickly becoming a center for retail automobile outlets, there are also many shops and businesses located downtown.  The largest indoor shopping mall even includes a movie theater, in addition to over 50 department and specialty stores and restaurants.  With so much to offer, Burlington is a prime location to visit and study! </p>
